text: Dame Quentin Alice Louise Bryce (n√©e Strachan; born 23 December 1942) was the 25th Governor-General of Australia, from September 2008 to March 2014. She was the first woman to be the Governor-General. Before this she was the Governor of Queensland and she used to be a lawyer. For her community works she was created a Dame of Grace of the Order of St John in 2003. If she were not already a Dame, she would have become a Dame of Justice when she became Prior of the Australian Priory of the Order of St John. ==References== Category:1942 births Category:Living people Category:Australian lawyers Category:Governors of Queensland Category:Governors-general of Australia Category:Politicians from Brisbane Category:Knights of Grace of the Order of St John Category:Order of Australia
